Text.Value: Very well! I wish you a safe journey. Perhaps I'll see you on the road to the Towers.
Wulbren needs a hero. Someone like you. And you need a way to protect yourself against the forces of evil, hm?
There's something in the air. I don't like it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Respnding to 'Perhaps what you're sensing is the shadowcurse'. Really, what Barcus is sensing is that Wulbren is dead.

Text.Value: Fortunately for me, you do. There was a rather compromising incident at a windmill, and another with some duergar.
Welcome to the club!
But... Wulbren? Dead?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Barcus faints at the end of the node
EditorData.NodeContext: Player has just told Barcus that Wulbren is dead, and Barcus is trying to make sense of it. He's about to faint.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KB][Foley] Thump as Barcus collapses on the ground from fainting

Text.Value: There's a recipe I'm trying to replicate. Something that might help you.

EditorData.NodeContext: He's a bit shy about being vulnerable by being friendly to you, but trying to play it cool

Text.Value: Do as you wish, but I won't rescue you a third time.
...dead?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Barcus faints at the end of the node
EditorData.NodeContext: Losing consciousness, about to faint
EditorData.SFXTags: [KB][Foley] Thump as Barcus collapses on the ground from fainting

Text.Value: Nasty place, isn't it. My torch only just held out long enough for me to find my way here.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* [Barcus] CINE_Turn. various optiond depending on scene set-up. <ChrisW>
EditorData.NodeContext: He turns to face the player

Text.Value: What will you do now?
A new type of smokepowder. All the bang and boom of the original, but with an extra surprise. I call it the Brilliant Retort.
That is - if you're still going to help Wulbren and the others.
Indeed. I found this place on my way to Moonrise Towers.
Yes?

EditorData.NodeContext: Normal affect, Barcus' version of a decent mood

Text.Value: The Brilliant Retort is ready. It's yours.
You'll need it if you're going to save Wulbren.

EditorData.NodeContext: A quiet, intimate plea encased with his stoicism.

Text.Value: But - that's for me to worry about.
Are you joking? Barcus, Wulbren is right in the other room.
I don't think so.
I'll get to work on the Brilliant Retort. You get to work at the Towers. Deal?
Leave.
It's up to you. You're the only one capable of it. Crush them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Cold edge

Text.Value: Where in the world did everyone go? Quite the fuss, but I'm not sure why. You'll - you'll follow up, keep things in hand, won't you? Of course you will.
I don't know what you mean.
Huh? It... seems to have disappeared.
Then again... if you're going to the Towers... it stands to reason you might encounter Wulbren while you're there.
I was about to ask you the same. I'm going to Moonrise Towers in search of my friend Wulbren.
Go on, then. No one but hang-abouts and n'er-do-muches here. And myself, of course.
But! I won't stand idle. I've spotted an alchemist's scales and had already been cooking up a little something that might help against those cultists.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wants to be useful, getting back to his old perfunctory self.

Text.Value: Who's Wulbren?
What now?

EditorData.NodeContext: Mild irritation

Text.Value: Nor have I. Everything in its due course, hmm? First, the Brilliant Retort. Then, Wulbren. Then, your reward.
Very good, very good. Very good indeed!
Oh, joy. More cultists.
Ah, of course. How are things, Barcus?
I'll... well. I'll... I'm not sure.

EditorData.NodeContext: Response to 'what will you do now that Wulbren's dead'. He cant fathom an answer

Text.Value: Or worse - to try your best and end up hurting the one you love the most.
Wulbren?
Perhaps we ought to allocate our resources intelligently. According to our talents, as it were.
I haven't forgotten. And as it happens, I was making something to help you on your way.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* [Barcus] CINE_Turn. various optiond depending on scene set-up. <ChrisW>
EditorData.NodeContext: He's quite excited by what you've said, but trying to play it down in classic Barcus fashion. He turns around on 'And as it happens, I was making something to help you on your way.'

Text.Value: If anyone can, I'm sure it's you.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* [Barcus] CINE_Turn. various optiond depending on scene set-up. <ChrisW>
EditorData.NodeContext: He turns to face the player here. He's sincere, but deadpan in his delivery. He's not one to betray emotion, but he does speak facts unbegrudgingly.

Text.Value: A new type of smokepowder. All the bang and boom of the original, but with an extra surprise. Guaranteed to end any and all arguments or protestations.
What's 'the Brilliant Retort'?
A new type of smokepowder. I call it the Brilliant Retort. It's yours! Now - I need to go find Wulbren!
When I'm finished making it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyance.

Text.Value: An old friend. The kind one doesn't simply leave to his own reckless fate - even when it leads to the heart of a murderous cult!

EditorData.NodeContext: With a twinge of irony. Barcus realizes he's being a bit excessive in pursuing Wulbren this far, but there's no 2 ways about it. He'd do anything to save his dumbass friend.

Text.Value: I say, are you quite all right? You look a little peaky.
Leave.
I'm sure I'll come up with... something.

EditorData.NodeContext: Losing confidence in his own abilities.

Text.Value: If he's there, I plan to find him.
What are you doing here, anyway?
An old friend. The kind one doesn't simply leave to his own reckless fate - even when it leads to the heart of a murderous cult.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a twinge of irony. Barcus realizes he's being a bit excessive in pursuing Wulbren this far, but there's no 2 ways about it. He'd do anything to save his dumbass friend.

Text.Value: Aren't you some kind of wandering hero? Isn't this what you do?

EditorData.NodeContext: Irritated.

Text.Value: That seems likely. Everyone loves providing refuge for a poor, defenceless deep gnome.

EditorData.NodeContext: Putting on a bit of an act, miming helplessness that masks his cynicism

Text.Value: You understand correctly. But it would be suicide for you to go near the place.
Then it's settled. You stay here. I'll search the Towers.
I'm afraid he didn't make it.
I call it the Brilliant Retort. Seems a bit glib now - but it would've made Wulbren smile, I think.
While you were infiltrating the Towers, I was working on something I thought might help in the fight against those cultists.

EditorData.logicalname: Can give BT / Doesn't know BT

Text.Value: Of course I am.
Oh. Yes. Hello.

EditorData.NodeContext: After he fainted, Barcus wakes up and is a bit unsteady. He remembers Wulbren is dead and is trying to process. A bit dissociated

Text.Value: Even if you get past the shadow curse, you'll never make it past that many cultists.
I thought I'd scout ahead. Check for any nasty surprises. Of which I found a great deal.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* [Barcus] CINE_Turn. various optiond depending on scene set-up. <ChrisW>
EditorData.NodeContext: Grave but wry; Barcus turns to face the player

Text.Value: Don't threaten me with a good time. My search for Wulbren has been one quagmire after another, as you know.
I did what you asked. Ready for my reward.
No. And pestering the craftsman won't speed things up!
There's nothing I can do. It's over.
Here - take this - quickly.

EditorData.NodeContext: Urgently wants to go find Wulbren, who's been found; happy.

Text.Value: I like the name. What's it do?
Haven't you heard? I freed the people being held in Moonrise Towers.
I'd like to trade.
Give me the schematics for the Brilliant Retort and we have a deal.
Hello, Barcus. How are things?
We'll see.
I'm sure I'll have no problem locating Wulbren and skipping out of there hand in hand!

EditorData.NodeContext: sarcasm

Text.Value: Are you following me?
Ah - you found your way. Good.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: As the player approaches, Barcus is still facing his work bench, inspecting beakers of powder in the light. With his back turned to player, without looking up, he addresses the player..

Text.Value: I hope you got a warmer welcome than I.
Whatever you say.

EditorData.NodeContext: REplying to player who is denying that anything's the matter.

Text.Value: That's very decent of you. Very decent of you indeed.

EditorData.NodeContext: Quite grateful but not used to showing it.

Text.Value: Take it. And give the Absolute hell.

EditorData.NodeContext: With a cold edge; anger at hte death of Wulbren sinking in. Disgust on 'the Absolute'

Text.Value: It helps to know when to close your eyes and run. I bumped into this inn before any nasty shadows got their tendrils on me.
Wulbren got himself into this mess. It isn't your fault.
I don't know. I can't help but feel that something's... especially wrong. I mustn't let my imagination run away with me, though.
Your work here isn't done. So perhaps you should get on with it.
I went to Moonrise Towers. All the captives there have perished.
Do I know you?
Deal.
I thought that was your mission.
They didn't get trapped, they were kidnapped! Taken against their will by those cultists. If I ever get my hands on one of them... well. With you on the job, perhaps I won't have to find out.
I'm sure you would!

EditorData.NodeContext: in response to "I'd like to trade"

Text.Value: I suppose I've earned the reputation. I'll help find your friends.
If anyone can, I'm certain it's you. But you won't do it alone. I'm working on a recipe to help you on your way.
Seems you've found yourself in another scrape.
You're on your own.
You - you did? But that means... Wulbren!

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* [Barcus]CINE_TurnLeft180_toJog_StandR_01 or similar depending on the direction<Greg>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He runs off from the player to go find Wulbren, who's in the other room.
EditorData.NodeContext: Surprised and excited
EditorData.logicalname: Will give reward after wulbren chat

Text.Value: You, on the other hand, have proven resourceful in such infiltrations.
What a brutal horror this life can be.
Leave.
There are deep gnomes being held in Moonrise Towers. One of them is my friend Wulbren.
I'll leave you to consider it.
How are things? How are things?
Let's not ruin the surprise, hmm?
Is it true? About Wulbren?

EditorData.NodeContext: He's terrified and heartbroken but trying to hold it together.

Text.Value: What happened to the other gnomes you were with?
A terrible thing, isn't it? A terrible thing, to try your best and get nowhere at all.
Go on.
Hmm?

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad, post poor outcome for Wulbren

Text.Value: Everyone seems to be quite a-flutter. Do you know why?
That's what the others said. And yet... and yet... how could it be?

EditorData.NodeContext: Reeling, having just heard Wulbren is dead. He's having trouble wrappng his head around this. Decimated.

Text.Value: How could it...?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Barcus faints at the end of the node
EditorData.NodeContext: Woozy, losing consciousness, full line would be 'How could it be that Wulbren is dead?'
EditorData.SFXTags: [KB][Foley] Thump as Barcus collapses on the ground from fainting

Text.Value: You - you do whatever it is you do.

EditorData.NodeContext: Waving the player away.

Text.Value: I told you I'd help rescue Wulbren and the others - this is my first stop.

EditorData.logicalname: If player accepted quest to help gnomes

Text.Value: Ah. You.
Anything I can do to help?
Perished... but that means... but Wulbren. How could it be...?
He - wha - you're - excuse me.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* [Barcus]CINE_TurnLeft180_toJog_StandR_01 or similar depending on the direction<Greg>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He runs off from the player to go find Wulbren, who's in the other room.
EditorData.NodeContext: Disbelief, then excitement as he realizes Wulbren is in the other room
EditorData.logicalname: Will give reward after wulbren chat

Text.Value: I'll soon be off to Moonrise Towers to look for my friend Wulbren. I understand you might be headed in that direction as well.
It's new type of smokepowder. Plenty of firepower in it, but with an extra surprise. Sure to take those cultists down a short road, if you catch my meaning.
But with a little luck, perhaps I won't.
I have reason to believe the seat of the Absolute is in Moonrise.
And what did you find?
Oh... well...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Barcus faints at the end of the node
EditorData.NodeContext: GEtting ready to faint, then faints
EditorData.SFXTags: [KB][Foley] Thump as Barcus collapses on the ground from fainting

Text.Value: Leave.
Dear me. That's quite a loss. But! Oh well! Wulbren's back!
Wulbren's gone. Wulbren's... dead. But. You know that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Trying to put all the facts together, through the shock of losing Wulbren

Text.Value: How can it be? I failed him so utterly.
Some of us are counting on you.

EditorData.NodeContext: softening, very slightly

Text.Value: Could be the evil curse surrounding us.
What are you doing here?

EditorData.NodeContext: answering 'you were supposed to wait at camp.'

Text.Value: Talk to your friends about it. It's none of my business.
Then again, my track record is... well. Discouraging.

EditorData.NodeContext: Coming around, realizing he might not be best-suited to find Wulbren.

EditorData.stateContext: Barcus is standing, facing his workbench, with his back to player.

Text.Value: In that case, you'll be very pleased to learn what I have in store for you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Chuffed

Text.Value: I'll do my part according to my talents, and you, I hope, will do yours.
I seek not promises, my friend, but deeds worthy of your prodigious talents.

EditorData.NodeContext: He's haphazardly using flattery; he's not used to resorting to it.

Text.Value: Still. A friend is a friend. And Wulbren won't last long in a place as dreadful as the Towers.
I'll keep an eye out for your friends, but no promises.
I can't tell if you're my good luck charm, or an omen of my every misfortunate.
That bloody cult has taken too much. They need to be stopped.
I have more important things to do.
Pah! Wulbren's a... parochial sort. The mere sight of you would knock him out cold.
I'm certain Wulbren's never met a half-orc. He'd probably think you're a hallucination.
A duergar saviour? Pah! Wulbren wouldn't understand the concept.
Pah! The mere sight of a dragonborn would scare him senseless.
You wouldn't even know what he looks like.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dismissive

Text.Value: The deep gnomes at the Towers, of course! And Wulbren among them, if he's to be found.

EditorData.NodeContext: Irritated.

Text.Value: So, so utterly.
Eh.
I did - though with a few hiccups along the way.
Depends. What did you say you were making?
It didn't seem right to let you do all the work. And as it happens, I've cobbled together something of an alchemist's workbench here in this inn.
Sounds good. But I haven't forgotten you also promised me a reward once I've saved your friend.
Well. I've been through worse.
It's too late for Wulbren. For me. But not for others. Nor for you.
Please. I'll make it extra explosive. Just for you.
Friends. And Wulbren. He... he...
I'm going to Moonrise Towers, too. Why don't you let me look for him.
Out of one, really. It took a bit of nimble footwork to make it through the darkness un-cursed.
Don't know. Don't care.
Now, if you're done rifling through my things...
You mean - but that means - Wulbren.
When will it be ready?
I'll bear that in mind.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sarcastic. In response to the player being snarky.

Text.Value: Luckily, I found this place. As have you.

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit dry

Text.Value: Especially the Absolute.
What's that you're making?
And you're doing... general heroism, I believe it is?
Wulbren who?
What's next on your agenda?
Shades. Death. Harpers. Flaming Fist. And this, of course. And the makings of an alchemist's workbench. Ingredients, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grim, but at the mention of the workbench he can't help but light up a little. He's an inventor at heart and is very enthused.

Text.Value: Seems you can handle things yourself.
I give you: The Brilliant Retort! Now - I need to go find Wulbren!
I decided to scout ahead and get the lay of the land.
I help a lot of people - remind me who you mean?
Ah. There you are.
I'm sorry, Barcus - Wulbren is dead.
Not now - Wulbren's back!

EditorData.NodeContext: Can't hide his excitement

Text.Value: He should never have joined those bloody Ironhand Gnomes. I told him, and I told him, and I told him. And now? Now he's dead.
You'll need it if you're going to get into Moonrise Towers and help the deep gnomes taken prisoner there.
Wait! Wait. I may be proud, but I'm no fool. If Wulbren is to be found, you stand the best chance of finding him.

Let's call a thing a thing: a deep gnome won't get far into the Absolute's orgy of evil. We already learned that in the Underdark with those sadistic duergar, didn't we? It's doubly true in this place.
I don't work for free. Throw in the plans for what you're working on and I'll consider.
The Brilliant Retort will aid you. Thus, I will make it.
How did you make your way through the shadows?
What's that you're making?
You'll need it if you're going to survive this cursed place.
The cult has probably taken him for parts by now. Oh well.
If you'll agree to look for him, I'll make myself useful here. I've spotted an alchemist's scales and had already been dreaming up a little something to help fight off those loathsome cultists.
A friend. I'd do anything to find him. Including trusting his fate to the likes of you.

EditorData.NodeContext: He softens. His 'insult' to the player isn't serious. He knows you're his best bet and he says this wryly, not meant to insult.

Text.Value: Hadn't expected to find this place. I'm trying to get into the Towers.
Is the Brilliant Retort ready?

A-ha. I was hoping you'd find this place. Thought you might've fallen in a hole. I'm pleased to see you, but I think there's something happening at the Towers. You like heroism, don't you? Might be of interest.
Disappointment. The raisin cookie of the soul.
Now, I've only to find my way into the Towers...
Whatever it is, I'm sure the rescue of a few innocent citizens will round it out nicely.
How did deep gnomes get trapped in the Towers?
Now! You - off to your... heroism, as it were.
Don't be ridiculous - if I give you the schematics, how in all of Toril am I supposed to make the damn thing?
Unless you've got access to a 300-year-old Tempusian apothecarial almanac, no.

Synopsis:
The unfortunate gnome is playing with his powders, his mood downcast and face smeared with soot. He's learnt that the gnomes are at Moonrise. He'll ask us again to help them if we haven't agreed already. He has nodes to cover alternate states in HAV, but not as many as e.g. harpers. He is mostly concerned with Wulbren, and other matters are of little import to him.
This dialogue will be expanded when we have clear messaging around what happened to the gnomes in HAV and how Barcus should react to them.
